We are our own virus, it seems; we just haven’t learned anything. Yes, we wear our masks and gloves to help stop the spread of the coronavirus, but we still have the culture of dumping … used masks and gloves are carelessly thrown away in the street. Don’t people realise kids pick them up to play with them? They even bring them home, unbeknown to their families. Yes, children aren’t supposed to be in the streets but, believe me, I see them every day playing where they shouldn’t. Just as I see used masks and gloves littering the streets. Some...